issues.text: whether the application was made within the time prescribed by the Limitation Act

anchor.surface_text: SARKAR J.-This appeal arises out of an application for execution of a decree for money and the only question is whether the application was made within the time prescribed by the Limitation Act.

issues.text: The question for determination is whether the fifth point of time applies to the receivers application for execution

anchor.surface_text: Applications for execution like the present one are governed by art. 182 of the Limitation Act. That article provides a period of three years within which the application must be made. The article prescribes different points of time for different cases from which the period is to commence running. The first point of time so prescribed is the date of the decree. The fifth point of time prescribed is expressed in these words  Where the application next hereinafter mentioned has been made  the date of the final order passed on an application made in accordance with law to the proper court for execution The question for determination is whether the fifth point of time applies to the receivers application for execution.
